  <entry>
    <title>Self-Check Card 🧷 吾日三省吾身</title>
    <link href="https://ashburshui.github.io/2021/01/17/caprice/self_check_card_%E5%90%BE%E6%97%A5%E4%B8%89%E7%9C%81%E5%90%BE%E8%BA%AB/"/>
    <id>https://ashburshui.github.io/2021/01/17/caprice/self_check_card_%E5%90%BE%E6%97%A5%E4%B8%89%E7%9C%81%E5%90%BE%E8%BA%AB/</id>
    <published>2021-01-17T14:48:03.000Z</published>
    <updated>2021-04-05T07:53:12.411Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<blockquote><p>Think and reflect, how to make my life better?<br><a id="more"></a></p></blockquote><p>I encounter several fantastic quotes,</p><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">&quot;生命如此短暂, 我们没有时间去互相争吵, 道歉, 发泄, 责备, 时间只够用来去爱, 可它又只有一瞬, 令人惋惜!&quot;</span><br><span class="line">                                                                        </span><br><span class="line">                                                                           ——马克·吐温</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Life is hard, but from what I have learned so far, the journey to happiness is also the journey towards growth mindset. No matter what happens, always think about the following questions,</p><blockquote><p>What have I learned?<br>How can I do better next time？</p></blockquote><p>If I don’t blame, then each experience is a learning process rather a permanent failure label, right? This is the core of happy life.</p>]]></content>
    
    <summary type="html">
    
      &lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Think and reflect, how to make my life better?&lt;br&gt;
    
    </summary>
    
    
    
  </entry>
  
  <entry>
    <title>The Ultimate Secret From Sage</title>
    <link href="https://ashburshui.github.io/2020/07/20/caprice/the_ultimate_secret_from_sage/"/>
    <id>https://ashburshui.github.io/2020/07/20/caprice/the_ultimate_secret_from_sage/</id>
    <published>2020-07-20T14:03:27.000Z</published>
    <updated>2020-10-16T02:14:50.918Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<blockquote><p>Cultivate myself, towards a better and more rational person… It’s a life-long persuit!<br><a id="more"></a></p><p>Think about the quote over and over again, do frequent retrospection and think about what’s the next step.</p></blockquote><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">&quot;You don&#39;t have a lot of envy.&quot;</span><br><span class="line">&quot;You don&#39;t have a lot of resentment.&quot;</span><br><span class="line">&quot;You don&#39;t overspend your income.&quot;</span><br><span class="line">&quot;You stay cheerful in spite of your troubles.&quot;</span><br><span class="line">&quot;You deal with reliable people.&quot;</span><br><span class="line">&quot;And you do what you&#39;re supposed to do.&quot;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">And all these simple rules work so well to make your life better. And they&#39;re so trit</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">- Charlie Munger</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Just love it, I think this quote is “the ultimate secret” behind happiness. </p>]]></content>
    
    <summary type="html">
    
      &lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cultivate myself, towards a better and more rational person… It’s a life-long persuit!&lt;br&gt;
    
    </summary>
    
    
    
